In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims the third Saturday of each May as Armed Forces Day. He pays tribute to the men and women in the military who put their lives on the line to protect and serve the country. He acknowledges their heroism and the sacrifices they have made in defending the nation. The president emphasizes the importance of supporting the troops both during their missions abroad and when they return home. He calls on citizens to show their appreciation by displaying the American flag at their homes on Armed Forces Day and encourages them to learn more about military service and volunteer at organizations that support the military and their families.